Sekhukhune United have announced the signings of experienced trio Justin Shonga, EvansRusike and LuckyBoy Mokoena. Shonga, the former Orlando Pirates striker, joins Babina Noko after a brief spell with Egyptian side Ismaily SC. Rusike has been snapped up after a spell without a club having left Supersport United FC while defender LuckyBoy Mokoena joins from TS Galaxy. Born in Chipata, Zambia, Shonga (25) spent the last four years playing in South Africa for Pirates, Tshakhuma Tsha Madzivhandila and Cape Town City FC. Rusike, the 31-years old Zimbabwean international, started his career in 2010 with Kiglon before moving to Zimbabwe Saints in 2012. The 28-year-old Mokoena who hails from Koppies, Mpumalanga started his youth football career with Mpumalanga Black Aces, Kaizer Chiefs and Bidvest Wits, before playing senior football for Chippa United, Ubuntu Cape Town, Real Kings, Highlands Park and TS Galaxy. Shonga said “It is an awesome feeling to be back in the DStv Premiership. “However, the environment is totally different to Ismaily in the Egyptian Soccer League. "The Egyptian environment is conducive to focus on football. South Africa is more suitable to play football because I feel at home. My main priority is to help the team to accumulate more points going forward to finish in a respectable position. However, I will work hard to get my form back so that I can contribute immensely to the team’s success.” Mokoena said that he would like thank Sekhukhune United Technical Team and Management to be part of Sekhukhune United FC. He also indicated that he would work hard to contribute to the team’s success. His aim with the team is to win some silverwares. Rusike revealed that he is looking forward to the exciting season. He will do his best to ensure that Babina Noko stays where it belongs. he’s excited to be part of Babina Noko’s family. However, he is going to work hard to maintain the good image of the team. 